    <h1>A SOOTH&#xAD;ING LIS&#xAD;TEN POP</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201211/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-11"><time>2020-12-11</time></a>
        - <span>WEEKEND</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>NEG­A­TIVE Al­fred Hui</p>
    <p>Fee­ble­ness, Hate and Pain are some of the tracks on Hong Kong singer Al­fred Hui’s (above) lat­est Can­tonese al­bum, Neg­a­tive.</p>
    <p>While the al­bum and track names sound gloomy, Hui’s sooth­ing voice on this well-constructe­d work is a plea­sure to lis­ten to.</p>
    <p>On Lie, it trem­bles with hurt and be­trayal. And it is filled with pen­sive emo­tion on Fear.</p>
    <p>But not all the songs are bleak. Fee­ble­ness is about re­sist­ing one’s weak­nesses and find­ing the courage to keep fight­ing. This is an al­bum that is not afraid to ex­plore the dark­ness, but knows how to pull the lis­tener back into the light.</p>

